---
title: W43-Market-Miso Chili Chicken Wraps with Shredded Carrots
description: Obsessed with miso? Us too. That’s why we’re keeping all that precious umami flavor safe and sound in these miso chili chicken wraps! Fully cooked chicken breasts are chopped and tossed in a savory mix of miso sauce, spicy-sweet chili sauce, ponzu, and peanut butter. Next up, chicken and shredded carrots are wrapped up tight in a soft and secure tortilla. A tasty lunch AND peace of mind? Now that’s a wrap.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6319f433eba8ba33980947ac-913cbb1f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/miso-chili-chicken-wraps-6319f433eba8ba33980947ac-76b6fa7d.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: Asian
time required: 10 minutes
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/market/miso-chili-chicken-wraps-6319f433eba8ba33980947ac
nutrition:
  calories: 490 kcal
  fat: 14 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1360 mg
---

Dice @fully cooked chicken breasts{9%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Place in a large #microwave-safe bowl{}.

Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until warmed through, ~{90%seconds}.

In a medium microwave-safe bowl, combine @miso sauce concentrate{1%unit}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, @ponzu sauce{6%milliliters}, half the @peanut butter{1.15%ounce}, and @hot water{1%tbsp}. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave for ~{30-40%seconds}. Stir and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Transfer miso chili mixture to bowl with chicken. Toss to coat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Add miso chili chicken and @shredded carrots{4%ounce} to the bottom half of each tortilla. Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between #plates{} and serve.